    <h1>Commercial & Institutional AV</h1>
    <p class="dek">Presentation, display, and control systems for corporate, healthcare, retail, sports, and entertainment spaces.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<section class="block">
  <div class="wrap">
    <p>Magna-Tech designs and installs AV, video display, and control systems for a wide range of commercial and institutional spaces — corporate boardrooms, operations and control rooms, hospital training facilities, retail environments, sports venues, and visitor attractions. Each venue type has its own equipment and workflow, but the underlying job is the same: get the right image and sound in front of the right audience, with controls simple enough for non-technical staff to run day to day.</p>

    <p><strong>What we supply.</strong> Video conferencing and presentation displays for boardrooms and briefing rooms; video wall and multi-source switching systems for control and operations centers; auditorium and training-room AV for healthcare facilities; digital signage and multimedia advertising displays for retail; video board and sound systems for stadiums and arenas; and single- to multi-screen projection, including synchronized and 4K stacked systems, for visitor centers and attractions.</p>

    <p>One example: the Kimmel Center in Philadelphia, PA runs on a Barco DP4K-32B 4K digital projection package MTE supplied for its performance and event spaces — the same commercial-grade projection and control approach that carries over to boardrooms, control rooms, and attraction venues at a smaller scale. See the full <a href="/portfolio/">Portfolio</a> for more examples across venue types.</p>

    <h2 id="corporate">Corporate</h2>
    <p>Video conferencing, presentation displays, and control systems for boardrooms and briefing rooms — specified so a non-technical staff member can run the room without a technician on hand.</p>

    <h2 id="control-rooms">Control Rooms</h2>
    <p>Video wall, multi-source switching, and control systems for broadcast, security, and operations centers, built for reliability and long, continuous operating hours.</p>

    <h2 id="healthcare">Health Care</h2>
    <p>AV systems for hospital and healthcare-facility auditoriums, training rooms, and patient-facing displays.</p>

    <h2 id="shopping-malls">Shopping Malls</h2>
    <p>Internal and external multimedia advertising displays and digital signage systems for retail and shopping-center environments.</p>

    <h2 id="sport-venues">Sport Venues</h2>
    <p>Video board and sound systems for stadiums and arenas, sized to the venue and viewing distances.</p>

    <h2 id="entertainment">Entertainment</h2>
    <p>Projection and AV systems for visitor centers, attractions, and entertainment venues — from a single screen to synchronized multi-projector and 4K stacked systems.</p>

    <h2>Common questions</h2>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can one system handle both video conferencing and presentations in the same room?</summary>
      <p>Yes — most boardroom and briefing-room installs combine both on one control system, so staff switch between a video call and a presentation without touching separate equipment.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Do control-room systems need to run continuously?</summary>
      <p>Usually, yes. We spec video wall and switching equipment rated for long, uninterrupted operating hours rather than intermittent office use.</p>
    </details>
    <details class="faq-item">
      <summary>Can digital signage in a shopping mall be updated remotely?</summary>
      <p>Yes, the multimedia and signage systems we design support remote content updates so on-site staff don't need to touch the hardware to change what's displayed.</p>
    </details>

